      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions match COU operating envelope (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) within stated tolerances. All 5 operating points covered.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments performed at 37°C with bovine blood (hematocrit 30%). COU requires human blood at 37–38°C (hematocrit 35–45%). Species and hematocrit differences introduce unquantified hemolysis model bias. Only 3 of 5 COU operating points have matched experimental conditions. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., U95 validation metric per ASME V&V 20) applied to hemolysis QoI. Systematic bias and random error separated. Validation uncertainty documented.",
      "rationale": "MAE computed but ASME V&V 20 validation metric E not formally computed. Systematic bias not separated from random scatter. 2 of 5 operating points exceed experimental uncertainty bounds by 12–18%. Achieved level 2."
    },
